Here's a darned simple MATLAB script to calculate equilibrium 
products in an insulated hydrogen-air bomb. You'll have to watch your 
peak temperatures closely to make sure you stay in range of your 
species definitions (constant V combustion gets hot since no work is 
performed expanding the products).

G = gri30;
set(G,'X','H2:1,O2:2,N2:7.52','T',300,'P',101325)
equilibrate(G,'UV')

If you're interested in a flame propagating through a pre-mixed 
gasoline-fuel mixture in an engine cylinder you'll want something a 
bit more complex than this. Bill Reynold's ICE code (or any number of 
others) would be a good place to start for that. But I hope this 
gives you a staring point. 

Good luck.
Chad
